<paragraph id="9273A26EFFFDFFCAFF39FD063B09F848" blockId="1.[151,1437,259,2014]" pageId="1" pageNumber="144">
<emphasis id="A0B87E7CFFFDFFCAFF39FD063BF0F9BC" bold="true" box="[199,491,655,681]" pageId="1" pageNumber="144">Description. Both sexes.</emphasis>
Colour yellow to reddish brown. Idiosoma oval and somewhat flattened. Integument with wrinkled lineation. Idiosomal chaetome typical for the family 
<taxonomicName id="55CCD9EDFFFDFFCAFC35FD3A3F2CF9D8" authority="(Tuzovskij 1987)" baseAuthorityName="Tuzovskij" baseAuthorityYear="1987" box="[971,1335,691,717]" class="Arachnida" family="Sperchontidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Prostigmata" pageId="1" pageNumber="144" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">
Sperchontidae (
<bibRefCitation id="F65DDF9FFFFDFFCAFB84FD3A3F35F9D8" author="Tuzovskij, P. V." box="[1146,1326,691,717]" pageId="1" pageNumber="144" refId="ref3990" refString="Tuzovskij, P. V. (1987) Morfologiya i postembrional'noe razvitiye vodyanykh kleshchej [Morphology and Postembryonic Development in Water Mites]. Nauka Publ., Moscow, 172 pp. [in Russian]" type="book" year="1987">Tuzovskij 1987</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. Dorsum (
<figureCitation id="0AF7BEEBFFFDFFCAFF5EFD5E3AF9F9E4" box="[160,226,727,753]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–2" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1912,1936]" captionTargetBox="[162,1431,926,1877]" captionTargetId="figure-297@2.[151,1436,921,1889]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–2. Sperchon (Sperchon) pesici sp. n., male: 1, idiosoma dorsal view; 2, idiosoma ventral view. Scale bar: 200 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4756110" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4756110/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="144">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
) with five pairs of dorsocentralia. Two anterior pairs of dorsocentral plates (dc.1 and dc.2) located lateral to trichobothria 
<emphasis id="A0B87E7CFFFDFFCAFEAEFD753B77F803" box="[336,364,764,790]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="144">Oi</emphasis>
, other three pairs of dorsocentral plates (dc.3–dc.5) occupy a central position, dc.1 occasionally separated in two parts. Both pairs of trichobothria (
<emphasis id="A0B87E7CFFFDFFCAFCEFFCA9392BF82C" box="[785,816,800,825]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="144">Fp</emphasis>
and 
<emphasis id="A0B87E7CFFFDFFCAFC97FCA9399EF82F" box="[873,901,800,826]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="144">Oi</emphasis>
) placed on small sclerites. Glandularia slightly developed.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="9273A26EFFFDFFCAFF39FCEE3F73F894" blockId="1.[151,1437,259,2014]" box="[199,1384,871,898]" pageId="1" pageNumber="144">
Anterior coxal groups with rounded medial margins and well separated, apodemes not developed (
<figureCitation id="0AF7BEEBFFFDFFCAFAE8FCEE3F40F894" box="[1302,1371,871,897]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–2" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1912,1936]" captionTargetBox="[162,1431,926,1877]" captionTargetId="figure-297@2.[151,1436,921,1889]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–2. Sperchon (Sperchon) pesici sp. n., male: 1, idiosoma dorsal view; 2, idiosoma ventral view. Scale bar: 200 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4756110" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4756110/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="144">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="9273A26EFFFDFFCAFF39FC023B7FFFD0" blockId="1.[151,1437,259,2014]" pageId="1" pageNumber="144">
Sclerites bearing setae 
<emphasis id="A0B87E7CFFFDFFCAFE32FC053BF6F8B0" box="[460,493,908,933]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="144">Hv</emphasis>
situated near posterolateral angles of coxae II. Posterior coxal groups widely separated, medial parts of coxae III narrow; glandularia 
<emphasis id="A0B87E7CFFFDFFCAFD1AFC393919F8DC" box="[740,770,944,969]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="144">Pe</emphasis>
open at anteromedial margin of coxae III. Setae 
<emphasis id="A0B87E7CFFFDFFCAFAD1FC393F53F8DC" box="[1327,1352,944,969]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="144">Pi</emphasis>
not associated with glandularia. Excretory pore without sclerotized ring, located anterior to setae 
<emphasis id="A0B87E7CFFFDFFCAFB69FC5D3ED1F8F8" box="[1175,1226,980,1006]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="144">Ci, s</emphasis>
etae 
<emphasis id="A0B87E7CFFFDFFCAFB00FC5A3F0FF8F8" box="[1278,1300,979,1005]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="144">Si</emphasis>
and 
<emphasis id="A0B87E7CFFFDFFCAFAB5FC5A3F7EF8F8" box="[1355,1381,979,1005]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="144">Se</emphasis>
posterolateral. There is one pair of ventral platelets situated laterally between setae 
<emphasis id="A0B87E7CFFFDFFCAFBE3FC713E2CFF07" box="[1053,1079,1016,1042]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="144">Ci</emphasis>
and 
<emphasis id="A0B87E7CFFFDFFCAFB8EFC7E3E91FF04" box="[1136,1162,1015,1041]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="144">Se</emphasis>
. Pregenital sclerite very small, postgenital sclerite comparatively large, elongate and unsclerotized. Genital field situated between posterior coxal groups, with three pairs of subequal acetabula which are distinctly separated (
<figureCitation id="0AF7BEEBFFFDFFCAFBA0FBB63EB2FF4C" box="[1118,1193,1087,1113]" captionStart="FIGURES 3–9" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1794,1818]" captionTargetBox="[166,1426,193,1766]" captionTargetId="figure-15@3.[151,1436,181,1770]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 3–9. Sperchon (Sperchon) pesici sp. n., male: 3, genital plate; 4, ejaculatory complex; 5, capitulum, lateral view; 6, chelicera, lateral view; 7, pedipalp; 8, IV-Leg-3–6; 9, leg claw. Scale bars: 3, 5–7 = 100 μm, 4 = 200 μm, 9 =50 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4756112" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4756112/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="144">Figs 3</figureCitation>
). Internal margins of genital flaps convex and cover only the second pair of acetabula completely. Each flap with 12–15 median and three to five fine lateral setae. Preginital sclerite very small, postgenital sclerite comparative large, somewhat elongate and unsclerotized.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="9273A26EFFFDFFCAFF39FB463E86FE1B" blockId="1.[151,1437,259,2014]" pageId="1" pageNumber="144">
Capitulum (
<figureCitation id="0AF7BEEBFFFDFFCAFEB3FB463B94FFFF" box="[333,399,1231,1258]" captionStart="FIGURES 3–9" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1794,1818]" captionTargetBox="[166,1426,193,1766]" captionTargetId="figure-15@3.[151,1436,181,1770]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 3–9. Sperchon (Sperchon) pesici sp. n., male: 3, genital plate; 4, ejaculatory complex; 5, capitulum, lateral view; 6, chelicera, lateral view; 7, pedipalp; 8, IV-Leg-3–6; 9, leg claw. Scale bars: 3, 5–7 = 100 μm, 4 = 200 μm, 9 =50 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4756112" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4756112/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="144">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
) with moderately long rostrum, ventral margin of rostrum convex. Both pairs of hypostomal setae subequal in length. Chelicera with large basal segment, chela crescent-shaped (
<figureCitation id="0AF7BEEBFFFDFFCAFBB5FB7A3E94FE1B" box="[1099,1167,1267,1294]" captionStart="FIGURES 3–9" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1794,1818]" captionTargetBox="[166,1426,193,1766]" captionTargetId="figure-15@3.[151,1436,181,1770]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 3–9. Sperchon (Sperchon) pesici sp. n., male: 3, genital plate; 4, ejaculatory complex; 5, capitulum, lateral view; 6, chelicera, lateral view; 7, pedipalp; 8, IV-Leg-3–6; 9, leg claw. Scale bars: 3, 5–7 = 100 μm, 4 = 200 μm, 9 =50 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4756112" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4756112/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="144">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="9273A26EFFFDFFCAFF39FA9E3B26FEF3" blockId="1.[151,1437,259,2014]" pageId="1" pageNumber="144">
Pedipalp (
<figureCitation id="0AF7BEEBFFFDFFCAFEC4FA9E3B6DFE27" box="[314,374,1303,1330]" captionStart="FIGURES 3–9" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1794,1818]" captionTargetBox="[166,1426,193,1766]" captionTargetId="figure-15@3.[151,1436,181,1770]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 3–9. Sperchon (Sperchon) pesici sp. n., male: 3, genital plate; 4, ejaculatory complex; 5, capitulum, lateral view; 6, chelicera, lateral view; 7, pedipalp; 8, IV-Leg-3–6; 9, leg claw. Scale bars: 3, 5–7 = 100 μm, 4 = 200 μm, 9 =50 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4756112" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4756112/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="144">Fig.7</figureCitation>
) stout, P-1 short and without setae; P-2 large, with six to eight stout dorsal setae, ventrodistal projecting moderately long conic and bearing two fine setae; P-3 moderately large maximum height near middle of segment, ventral margin straight longer than P-2, with three to five thick and two to four thin dorsal setae; P-4 slender and a little shorter than P-3, with several rather long dorsodistal and ventrodistal fine setae, ventral margin with two small tubercles bearing short peg-like seta each, proximal tubercle and peg-like seta a little larger than posterior ones.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="9273A26EFFFDFFCAFF39FA793BBEFD60" blockId="1.[151,1437,259,2014]" pageId="1" pageNumber="144">
Legs slender, especially posterior pair, III–IV-Leg-3–5 with several rather long dorsal plumose dorsal setae (
<figureCitation id="0AF7BEEBFFFDFFCAFF5EF99A3AF8FD38" box="[160,227,1555,1581]" captionStart="FIGURES 3–9" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1794,1818]" captionTargetBox="[166,1426,193,1766]" captionTargetId="figure-15@3.[151,1436,181,1770]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 3–9. Sperchon (Sperchon) pesici sp. n., male: 3, genital plate; 4, ejaculatory complex; 5, capitulum, lateral view; 6, chelicera, lateral view; 7, pedipalp; 8, IV-Leg-3–6; 9, leg claw. Scale bars: 3, 5–7 = 100 μm, 4 = 200 μm, 9 =50 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4756112" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4756112/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="144">Fig. 8</figureCitation>
). Leg claws (
<figureCitation id="0AF7BEEBFFFDFFCAFE89F99A3BA2FD38" box="[375,441,1555,1581]" captionStart="FIGURES 3–9" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1794,1818]" captionTargetBox="[166,1426,193,1766]" captionTargetId="figure-15@3.[151,1436,181,1770]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 3–9. Sperchon (Sperchon) pesici sp. n., male: 3, genital plate; 4, ejaculatory complex; 5, capitulum, lateral view; 6, chelicera, lateral view; 7, pedipalp; 8, IV-Leg-3–6; 9, leg claw. Scale bars: 3, 5–7 = 100 μm, 4 = 200 μm, 9 =50 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4756112" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4756112/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="144">Fig. 9</figureCitation>
) with three unequal, pointed clawlets,`dorsal clawlet longest, dorsal and median clawlets relatively thin, ventral clawlet with broad base and shorter than the anterior ones. Claw lamella well developed with concave ventral margin.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="9273A26EFFFDFFCAFF39F9F6389DFDA8" blockId="1.[151,1437,259,2014]" pageId="1" pageNumber="144">
<emphasis id="A0B87E7CFFFDFFCAFF39F9F63B10FD8C" bold="true" box="[199,267,1663,1689]" pageId="1" pageNumber="144">Male.</emphasis>
Ejaculatory complex proximal chamber large, proximal arms curved, broadest basally, tapering gradually to apex, distal arms slightly convex (
<figureCitation id="0AF7BEEBFFFDFFCAFDCDF92A3862FDA8" box="[563,633,1699,1725]" captionStart="FIGURES 3–9" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1794,1818]" captionTargetBox="[166,1426,193,1766]" captionTargetId="figure-15@3.[151,1436,181,1770]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 3–9. Sperchon (Sperchon) pesici sp. n., male: 3, genital plate; 4, ejaculatory complex; 5, capitulum, lateral view; 6, chelicera, lateral view; 7, pedipalp; 8, IV-Leg-3–6; 9, leg claw. Scale bars: 3, 5–7 = 100 μm, 4 = 200 μm, 9 =50 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4756112" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4756112/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="144">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="9273A26EFFFDFFCAFF39F94E3BFAFC80" blockId="1.[151,1437,259,2014]" pageId="1" pageNumber="144">Measurement(n=5). Idiosoma L 730–950; capitulum L 185–230, rostrum L 60–78; genital flap L 180–205, genital acetabula (ac.1–ac.3) L: 30–42, 42–48, 30–42; cheliceral segments: base L 185–215, chela L 65–70; pedipalp segments (P-1–5) L: 30–40, 120–145, 160–180, 135–155, 25–30; legs segments L: I-Leg-1–6: 65–75, 105– 130, 105–125, 145–180, 160–190, 160–190; II-Leg-1–6: 65–75, 110–140, 115–125, 170–205, 185–230, 180–215; III-Leg-1–6: 65–80, 110–145, 120–150, 175–220, 205–255, 185–235; IV-Leg-1–6: 120–165, 160–195, 145–180, 260–235, 245–295, 220–260.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="9273A26EFFFDFFCAFF39F8163F6AFCAC" blockId="1.[151,1437,259,2014]" box="[199,1393,1951,1978]" pageId="1" pageNumber="144">
<emphasis id="A0B87E7CFFFDFFCAFF39F8163B3EFCAC" bold="true" box="[199,293,1951,1977]" pageId="1" pageNumber="144">Female.</emphasis>
External morphology similar to male but larger, anterior genital sclerite much larger than in male.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="9273A26EFFFDFFC9FF39F84D3BB2FA54" blockId="1.[151,1437,259,2014]" lastBlockId="2.[151,1437,150,897]" lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="145" pageId="1" pageNumber="144">Measurement (n=10). Idiosoma L 810–1300; genital flap L 185–215, genital acetabula (ac.1–ac.3) L: 35–54, 36–48, 36–48; capitulum L 210–245, rostrum L 70–80; cheliceral segments: base L 195–215, chela L 60–75; pedipalp segments (P-1–5) L: 32–45, 130–140, 170–190, 135–170, 27–32; legs segments: I-Leg-1–6: 65–75, 120–130, 110–115, 170–180, 195–205, 180–195; II-Leg-1–6: 65–75, 120–140, 129–130, 210–220, 220–230, 195–215; III- Leg-1–6: 65–80, 130–140, 130–150, 225–245, 250–270, 220–240; IV-Leg-1–6: 135–165, 175–205, 160–190, 310– 335, 285–310, 245–285.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="9273A26EFFFEFFC9FF39FEC23966FA70" blockId="2.[151,1437,150,897]" box="[199,893,331,357]" pageId="2" pageNumber="145">
<emphasis id="A0B87E7CFFFEFFC9FF39FEC23B71FA70" bold="true" box="[199,362,331,357]" pageId="2" pageNumber="145">Deutonymph.</emphasis>
See 
<bibRefCitation id="F65DDF9FFFFEFFC9FE5EFEC23878FA70" author="Tuzovskij, P. V." box="[416,611,331,357]" pageId="2" pageNumber="145" refId="ref4028" refString="Tuzovskij, P. V. (1990) Opredelitel' deitonimphs vodyanykh kleschey [Key to water mite deutonymphs]. Nauka, Moscow, 238 pp. [in Russian]" type="book" year="1990">Tuzovskij (1990)</bibRefCitation>
, as 
<taxonomicName id="55CCD9EDFFFEFFC9FD73FEC2396EFA70" authorityName="Sokolow" authorityYear="1940" box="[653,885,331,357]" class="Arachnida" family="Sperchonidae" genus="Sperchon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="145" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tridentatus">
<emphasis id="A0B87E7CFFFEFFC9FD73FEC2396EFA70" box="[653,885,331,357]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="145">Sperchon tridentatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="9273A26EFFFEFFC9FF39FEE63931FA9C" blockId="2.[151,1437,150,897]" box="[199,810,367,394]" pageId="2" pageNumber="145">
<emphasis id="A0B87E7CFFFEFFC9FF39FEE63B0CFA9C" bold="true" box="[199,279,367,393]" pageId="2" pageNumber="145">Larva.</emphasis>
See 
<bibRefCitation id="F65DDF9FFFFEFFC9FEB3FEE6380BFA9F" author="Tuzovskij, P. V." box="[333,528,367,394]" pageId="2" pageNumber="145" pagination="33 - 40" refId="ref4100" refString="Tuzovskij, P. V. (2006) Description of the water mite larva Sperchon tridentatus Sokolow (Acariformes. Sperchontidae). Zoologia bespozvonochnykh [Zoology invertebrates], 3 (1), 33 - 40. [in Russian] https: // doi. org / 10.15298 / invertzool. 03.1.03" type="journal article" year="2006">Tuzovskij (2006)</bibRefCitation>
, as 
<taxonomicName id="55CCD9EDFFFEFFC9FDC4FEE63938FA9C" authorityName="Sokolow" authorityYear="1940" box="[570,803,367,393]" class="Arachnida" family="Sperchonidae" genus="Sperchon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="145" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tridentatus">
<emphasis id="A0B87E7CFFFEFFC9FDC4FEE63938FA9C" box="[570,803,367,393]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="145">Sperchon tridentatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="DAD6F1E5FFFEFFC9FF39FE1A3B86F800" pageId="2" pageNumber="145" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="9273A26EFFFEFFC9FF39FE1A3ECFF990" blockId="2.[151,1437,150,897]" pageId="2" pageNumber="145">
<emphasis id="A0B87E7CFFFEFFC9FF39FE1A3B20FAB8" bold="true" box="[199,315,403,429]" pageId="2" pageNumber="145">Remarks.</emphasis>
The new species is similar to 
<taxonomicName id="55CCD9EDFFFEFFC9FD6DFE1A3932FAB8" authorityName="Sokolow" authorityYear="1940" box="[659,809,403,429]" class="Arachnida" family="Sperchonidae" genus="Sperchon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="145" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tridentatus">
<emphasis id="A0B87E7CFFFEFFC9FD6DFE1A3932FAB8" box="[659,809,403,429]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="145">S. tridentatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="55CCD9EDFFFEFFC9FC9FFE1A39DAFAB9" authorityName="Tuzovskij" authorityYear="2003" box="[865,961,403,429]" class="Arachnida" family="Sperchonidae" genus="Sperchon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="145" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="minor">
<emphasis id="A0B87E7CFFFEFFC9FC9FFE1A39DAFAB9" box="[865,961,403,429]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="145">S. minor</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName id="55CCD9EDFFFEFFC9FC2EFE1A3E9AFAB9" authority="Tuzovskij, 2021" authorityName="Tuzovskij" authorityYear="2021" box="[976,1153,403,429]" class="Arachnida" family="Sperchonidae" genus="Sperchon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="145" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pesici" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis id="A0B87E7CFFFEFFC9FC2EFE1A3E9AFAB9" box="[976,1153,403,429]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="145">Sperchon pesici</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="BB8BC307FFFEFFC9FB77FE1A3EDDFAB8" box="[1161,1222,403,429]" pageId="2" pageNumber="145" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
is similar to 
<taxonomicName id="55CCD9EDFFFEFFC9FAA2FE1A3AEDFAC4" authorityName="Sokolow" authorityYear="1940" class="Arachnida" family="Sperchonidae" genus="Sperchon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="145" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tridentatus">
<emphasis id="A0B87E7CFFFEFFC9FAA2FE1A3AEDFAC4" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="145">S. tridentatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the structure of the genital field and coxal plates, differences between the two species are found in the following characters (character states of 
<taxonomicName id="55CCD9EDFFFEFFC9FDA1FE5238EFFAE0" authorityName="Sokolow" authorityYear="1940" box="[607,756,475,501]" class="Arachnida" family="Sperchonidae" genus="Sperchon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="145" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tridentatus">
<emphasis id="A0B87E7CFFFEFFC9FDA1FE5238EFFAE0" box="[607,756,475,501]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="145">S. tridentatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
given in parentheses, data from 
<bibRefCitation id="F65DDF9FFFFEFFC9FB9DFE523F10FAE0" author="Sokolow, I. I." box="[1123,1291,475,501]" pageId="2" pageNumber="145" pagination="1 - 511" refId="ref3946" refString="Sokolow, I. I. (1940) [Hydracarina. Part I: Hydrachnellae. In: Fauna of the USSR. Paukoobraznye 5 (2). Nauka, Moscow-Leningrad, pp. 1 - 511. [in Russian]" type="book chapter" year="1940">Sokolow 1940</bibRefCitation>
): integument with muscle attachment sclerites (
<figureCitation id="0AF7BEEBFFFEFFC9FDEFFE763868F90C" box="[529,627,511,537]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–2" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1912,1936]" captionTargetBox="[162,1431,926,1877]" captionTargetId="figure-297@2.[151,1436,921,1889]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–2. Sperchon (Sperchon) pesici sp. n., male: 1, idiosoma dorsal view; 2, idiosoma ventral view. Scale bar: 200 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4756110" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4756110/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="145">Figs 1–2</figureCitation>
) (without muscle attachment sclerites,); P-2 distoventral projecting with two fine setae, (
<figureCitation id="0AF7BEEBFFFEFFC9FEB0FDAA3B88F928" box="[334,403,547,573]" captionStart="FIGURES 3–9" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1794,1818]" captionTargetBox="[166,1426,193,1766]" captionTargetId="figure-15@3.[151,1436,181,1770]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 3–9. Sperchon (Sperchon) pesici sp. n., male: 3, genital plate; 4, ejaculatory complex; 5, capitulum, lateral view; 6, chelicera, lateral view; 7, pedipalp; 8, IV-Leg-3–6; 9, leg claw. Scale bars: 3, 5–7 = 100 μm, 4 = 200 μm, 9 =50 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4756112" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4756112/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="145">Fig. 7</figureCitation>
) (with three setae, 
<figureCitation id="0AF7BEEBFFFEFFC9FD8EFDAA38DEF928" box="[624,709,547,573]" captionStart="FIGURES 22–26" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[227,1364,196,1904]" captionTargetId="figure-20@6.[206,1381,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 22–26. Sperchon, adults: S. tridentatus: 22, pedipalp; 23, leg claw (after Sokolow 1940); S. minor: 24, idiosoma, dorsal view; 25, idiosoma, ventral view; 26, pedipalp (after Tuzovsky 2003)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4756118" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4756118/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="145">Fig. 22</figureCitation>
); P-3 is stockier, maximum height near middle of segment (P-3 more slender, maximum height in proximal quarter); leg claws with three unequal clawlets, lamella ventral margin concave, 
<figureCitation id="0AF7BEEBFFFEFFC9FEFFFDE23B59F990" box="[257,322,619,645]" captionStart="FIGURES 3–9" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1794,1818]" captionTargetBox="[166,1426,193,1766]" captionTargetId="figure-15@3.[151,1436,181,1770]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 3–9. Sperchon (Sperchon) pesici sp. n., male: 3, genital plate; 4, ejaculatory complex; 5, capitulum, lateral view; 6, chelicera, lateral view; 7, pedipalp; 8, IV-Leg-3–6; 9, leg claw. Scale bars: 3, 5–7 = 100 μm, 4 = 200 μm, 9 =50 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4756112" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4756112/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="145">Fig. 9</figureCitation>
(leg claws with three subequal clawlets, lamella ventral margin straight, 
<figureCitation id="0AF7BEEBFFFEFFC9FB8AFDE23ED3F990" box="[1140,1224,619,645]" captionStart="FIGURES 22–26" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[227,1364,196,1904]" captionTargetId="figure-20@6.[206,1381,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 22–26. Sperchon, adults: S. tridentatus: 22, pedipalp; 23, leg claw (after Sokolow 1940); S. minor: 24, idiosoma, dorsal view; 25, idiosoma, ventral view; 26, pedipalp (after Tuzovsky 2003)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4756118" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4756118/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="145">Fig. 23</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="9273A26EFFFEFFC9FF39FD063B86F800" blockId="2.[151,1437,150,897]" pageId="2" pageNumber="145">
The integument in 
<taxonomicName id="55CCD9EDFFFEFFC9FE67FD063BE3F9BD" authorityName="Tuzovskij" authorityYear="2003" box="[409,504,655,681]" class="Arachnida" family="Sperchonidae" genus="Sperchon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="145" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="minor">
<emphasis id="A0B87E7CFFFEFFC9FE67FD063BE3F9BD" box="[409,504,655,681]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="145">S. minor</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with muscle attachment sclerites, dc.1 and dc.2 unsclerotized, dc.3 fused with glandulartia 
<emphasis id="A0B87E7CFFFEFFC9FF0BFD3A3B0CF9D8" box="[245,279,691,717]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="145">Sci</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="0AF7BEEBFFFEFFC9FED7FD3A3B65F9D8" box="[297,382,691,717]" captionStart="FIGURES 22–26" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[227,1364,196,1904]" captionTargetId="figure-20@6.[206,1381,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 22–26. Sperchon, adults: S. tridentatus: 22, pedipalp; 23, leg claw (after Sokolow 1940); S. minor: 24, idiosoma, dorsal view; 25, idiosoma, ventral view; 26, pedipalp (after Tuzovsky 2003)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4756118" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4756118/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="145">Fig. 24</figureCitation>
), P-2 distoventral projecting short and without fine setae, with single thick seta near base of projection (
<figureCitation id="0AF7BEEBFFFEFFC9FEE6FD5E3B77F9E7" box="[280,364,727,754]" captionStart="FIGURES 22–26" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[227,1364,196,1904]" captionTargetId="figure-20@6.[206,1381,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 22–26. Sperchon, adults: S. tridentatus: 22, pedipalp; 23, leg claw (after Sokolow 1940); S. minor: 24, idiosoma, dorsal view; 25, idiosoma, ventral view; 26, pedipalp (after Tuzovsky 2003)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4756118" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4756118/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="145">Fig. 26</figureCitation>
), ac.2 larger than ac.1 and ac.3, all acetabula slightly separated, excretory pore (
<figureCitation id="0AF7BEEBFFFEFFC9FB11FD5E3F5BF9E4" box="[1263,1344,726,753]" captionStart="FIGURES 22–26" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[227,1364,196,1904]" captionTargetId="figure-20@6.[206,1381,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 22–26. Sperchon, adults: S. tridentatus: 22, pedipalp; 23, leg claw (after Sokolow 1940); S. minor: 24, idiosoma, dorsal view; 25, idiosoma, ventral view; 26, pedipalp (after Tuzovsky 2003)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4756118" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4756118/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="145">Fig. 25</figureCitation>
) sclerotized (
<bibRefCitation id="F65DDF9FFFFEFFC9FF22FD723B8AF800" author="Tuzovskij, P. V." box="[220,401,763,789]" pageId="2" pageNumber="145" pagination="215 - 219" refId="ref4060" refString="Tuzovskij, P. V. (2003) Two new species of water mites of the genus Sperchon Kramer (Acariformes, Sperchontidae) from Central Asia. Acarina, 11 (2), 215 - 219." type="journal article" year="2003">Tuzovskij 2003</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
